# HEUREKA UI Recreation Plan

## Goal Description
Recreate the HEUREKA landing page and authentication paths based on the provided Replit site. The app is a modern real estate SaaS and needs a very clean, dynamic user interface crafted with React and Tailwind CSS. The app will include three main pages: the Home Landing Page, the Login Page, and the Registration Page.

## Proposed Changes
### Project Initialization
- Create a new project structure using Vite (React + TypeScript).
- Configure Tailwind CSS.
- Set up React Router for navigation between the 3 main pages.

### Base UI Components
#### [NEW] `src/index.css`
Setup specific color variables and Tailwind utilities to match the design.
- Primary colors: Navy Blue (`#0B1B3D`) and soft accents.
- Inter or similar sans-serif font family.

#### [NEW] `src/components/ui/Button.tsx`
Reusable button components considering the solid and outline variations seen in the UI.

#### [NEW] `src/components/ui/Input.tsx`
Reusable input components with label and appropriate focus states (`ring-primary`).

### Routing and Layouts
#### [NEW] `src/App.tsx`
React Router configuration mapping `/`, `/login`, and `/register`.

#### [NEW] `src/components/layout/Navbar.tsx`
Top navigation component with Brand Logo and quick auth links.

#### [NEW] `src/components/layout/Footer.tsx`
Simple bottom footer text as described on the Replit site.

#### [NEW] `src/components/layout/AuthLayout.tsx`
A split-screen layout wrapper for the Authentication screens (half image/call-to-action, half form).

### Pages
#### [NEW] `src/pages/Home.tsx`
The main landing page with:
- Background graphic with architectural grid lines.
- Hero section with the 'Nouveau...' badge and primary CTAs.
- Features section grid.

#### [NEW] `src/pages/Login.tsx`
Authentication page that fits within `AuthLayout`. Includes logic for standard form UI.

#### [NEW] `src/pages/Register.tsx`
Registration page that fits within `AuthLayout`. Includes standard registration fields.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` to ensure the project bundles perfectly without TypeScript errors.
- Run `npm run dev` and execute browser checks for visual alignment and responsiveness.

### Manual Verification
- Review aesthetics across the Home, Login, and Register routes.
- Verify micro-interactions: Hover states on buttons, input focus rings, smooth route transitions if any.
